data.enText: a large group of soldiers that forms part of an army, especially the one that existed in ancient Rome
a large number of people of one particular type

data.chText: 草本植物的医药效用数不胜数。
data.enText: The medical uses of herbs are legion.

value.def: A legion is a large group of soldiers who form one section of an army.

example.ex: ...the Sudan-based troops of the Libyan Islamic Legion...
example.tran: 利比亚伊斯兰军团驻扎在苏丹的部队

example.ex: The last of the Roman legions left Britain in AD 410.
example.tran: 罗马军团最后一支部队于公元410年离开英国。

value.def: A legion of people or things is a great number of them.

example.ex: His delightful sense of humour won him a legion of friends.
example.tran: 他的幽默风趣为他赢得了众多的朋友。

example.ex: ...a legion of stories about noisy neighbours.
example.tran: 有关吵闹的邻居的众多故事

value.def: If you say that things of a particular kind are legion, you mean that there are a great number of them.

example.ex: The number of women who become pregnant after adopting children is legion.
example.tran: 领养小孩后怀孕的妇女比比皆是。

value.tran: 比比皆是的；不胜枚举的；多如牛毛的
